The Oniru of Iru, Oba Abdulwasiu Gbolahan Lawal, has urged monarchs to work together for the growth of Lagos communities. The monarch spoke during a courtesy call on the Onishasha of Shasha, Oba Babatunde Akanbi in Alimosho Local Government Area. He said his visit was an opportunity for both monarchs to chart the way forward for Sasha and Iru lands. Pledging support for the growth of Shasha, Oba Lawal said he would bring on board the right hands to ensure Iru people and residentsâ€™ progress. At the event, Chairman, Committee on Agriculture, Lagos State House of Assembly, Mr Kehinde Joseph, appealed to the Oba of Iru to support the developmental efforts in Alimosho Constituency 2.